<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy — Pagistry"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  updated="June 24, 2026"
>
  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Pagistry (“we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses,
    and protects your information when you use our website builder, CMS, and related
    services (the “Service”). By using the Service, you agree to the practices
    described here.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information in a few ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><b>Account information</b> — your name, email address, and password when you create an account.</li>
    <li><b>Content</b> — the pages, components, and CMS data you create or upload.</li>
    <li><b>Usage data</b> — how you interact with the Service, such as features used and pages visited.</li>
    <li><b>Device data</b> — browser type, operating system, and approximate location derived from your IP address.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your information</h2>
  <p>
    We use your information to provide and improve the Service, authenticate your
    account, publish and host your sites, communicate with you about updates, and
    keep the Service secure. We do not sell your personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies &amp; tracking</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies and similar technologies to keep you signed in, remember your
    preferences, and understand how the Service is used. You can control cookies
    through your browser settings, though some features may not work without them.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing &amp; disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    We share information only with service providers who help us operate the Service
    (such as hosting and analytics providers), when required by law, or to protect
    the rights and safety of our users. These providers are bound by confidentiality
    obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Data security</h2>
  <p>
    We use encryption in transit, access controls, and regular reviews to protect
    your data. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, but we
    work hard to safeguard your information.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, export,
    or delete your personal information, and to object to certain processing. To
    exercise these rights, contact us using the details below.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
    “last updated” date above and, where appropriate, notify you within the Service.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy? Email us at
    <a href="mailto:privacy@pagistry.com">privacy@pagistry.com</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>
